# Most of the repo isn't needed for the bench image. The image
# is purely tools + a Rust toolchain; the actual alint source
# is bind-mounted at runtime via `-v $PWD:/work`. So .dockerignore
# is aggressive: only the Dockerfile itself reaches the build
# context.

# Allow nothing by default.
*

# Then re-include only the Dockerfile + this file.
!Dockerfile
!.dockerignore
